message.content: cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.BIO, cs.NEURON - The paper presents a novel deep learning approach for automatic function prediction of proteins using their primary sequence. This falls under the intersection of several sub-fields such as machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), bioinformatics (cs.BIO), and neural networks (cs.NEURON). The use of deep learning and neural networks in particular, along with the focus on protein function prediction, makes cs.LG and cs.NEURON the most likely sub-categories. The use of convolutional and recurrent networks also suggests cs.CV and cs.AI as possible sub-categories. Finally, the focus on bioinformatics and protein function prediction makes cs.BIO a likely sub-category as well.
